com.siperian.sif.message.mrm

Class AcceptUnmatchedRecordsAsUniqueRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianRequest
      • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianObjectRequest
        • com.siperian.sif.message.mrm.AcceptUnmatchedRecordsAsUniqueRequest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SiperianObjectUidProvider, Serializable

    public class AcceptUnmatchedRecordsAsUniqueRequest
extends SiperianObjectRequest
    Represents a request object to accept the unmatched records as unique records. The state of records that have no match candidates is changed from unmerged state to consolidated state. The unique records are removed from the manual review queue, and the automerge batch process cannot merge these records. However, you can use MergeRequest or the Hub Console to manually merge the records.

    Note: When you use the Audit Manager in the Hub Console, use AcceptUnmatchedRecordsAsUniqueRequest only for a system that is of 'no system' type. After you enable auditing for a request, the MDM Hub logs the request invocation and response in the audit log. For more information about auditing, see the Informatica Multidomain MDM Configuration Guide.

    Use Case

    In an application that has a custom UI for data stewards to manage the status of records, you can create a button that uses AcceptUnmatchedRecordsAsUniqueRequest to accept all the unmatched records as unique records.

    Usage Example

    AcceptUnmatchedRecordsAsUniqueRequest request = new
    AcceptUnmatchedRecordsAsUniqueRequest();
    request.setAssignedOnly(true);
    linkRecordKey.setSiperianObjectUid("PACKAGE.PARTY_UPDATE");
    AcceptUnmatchedRecordsAsUniqueResponse response = (AcceptUnmatchedRecordsAsUniqueResponse)sipClient.process(request);
    See Also:
    AcceptUnmatchedRecordsAsUniqueResponse, SiperianObjectRequest, SiperianObjectUidProvider, MergeRequest, Serialized Form

    API Pair: AcceptUnmatchedRecordsAsUniqueResponse

    API Group: Merge Workflow
